Casablanca,yG-lKxPb5yU,Ugx3MczSgysxH95VTbl4AaABAg,,@rizqbeckett7086,"What’s amazing about this movie is the things that I notice almost every time I watch it. I noticed that Ilsa has never told her husband that she loves him, although he often declares his love to her and not only in words, but she does say it to Rick. But there’s no denying that she admires her husband and it’s apparent why, in spite of the threats from the Nazis his courage and commitment is outstanding. There’s an incident that causes Rick to switch his mind from his original plan to allow Victor to get away alone without his wife. I think it’s when Victor unselfishly asks Rick to use the letters of transits to take his wife away after telling Rick to his face that he knows that he loves his wife too. I also think that Rick hated when Louie compared his low immoral self to him. The key word was when he asked her to trust him. Because in the next scene when Louie tried to arrest Victor….well the rest of the movie is perhaps one of the greatest endings in movie history with four words before walking away with Louie, “Here’s looking at you kid!”.",2026-05-08T12:55:58Z,2026-05-08T13:14:38Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-15T02:01:17.950016
