Casablanca,yG-lKxPb5yU,Ugw9iNzrBa3InPyKLeB4AaABAg.APwjvri7MJoAU7hJfotcYw,Ugw9iNzrBa3InPyKLeB4AaABAg,@gemanscombe4985,"""Kid"" was colloquial of the time, like ""kiddo"" and ""Bud"". Rick wasn't calling her a child or a young goat. Bogart was 42, playing 37. Bergman was 27, playing 20-something, not 15. From what I've read, ""Here's looking at you, kid"" was what Bogart said when playing poker and calling for the cards to be shown. He used it here as a toast or pet phrase of endearment.",2026-03-09T09:50:51Z,2026-03-09T09:50:51Z,0,True,,2026-05-15T02:01:19.166290
