Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg.AI8sQf1RvHxAJcg20wZ10Q,UgygZU6QQK-K6GiPyIt4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,Hi @cdeleo9336: TimS used the same tour as we did. Here's the link: https://www.airbnb.com/experiences/604421 —Judy,2025-06-21T10:10:04Z,2025-06-21T10:10:04Z,0,True,,2026-05-15T02:01:54.282180
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugwm-74gikWd5EmR78l4AaABAg.AHLlqV6Pq1XAHNERjUGT4q,Ugwm-74gikWd5EmR78l4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Muhammed, We LOVE London. In fact our daughter was just there two days ago after visiting with us in Malta! May will be a nice time to visit Marrakech. The weather is hot but not unbearable, especially if you avoid the hottest parts of the day. And May is a month of celebrations. The Kelaa M'Gouna or Festival of the Rose runs from May 5-9 if you will be around to attend that. Have a terrific time! —Judy",2025-04-26T07:49:32Z,2025-04-26T07:49:32Z,0,True,,2026-05-15T02:01:54.364985
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgxuUUq3xrtcndmn-Kx4AaABAg.AH93pO8FVUiAHDeSgIl9_t,UgxuUUq3xrtcndmn-Kx4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Laura, The culture in Morocco is more modest, so if you want to respect the local culture, you won't wear clothes that are too revealing. I'm wearing tank tops, and my skirts are close to knee length, but you could cover your arms with an airy blouse and wear loose long pants or long skirts. I wasn't going to go out and buy these items since we're full time travelers, but I tried to be as modest as possible given my limited wardrobe. Morocco is reasonably understanding of tourists and don't necessarily expect them to follow all the Muslim customs. Personally, I wouldn't wear crop tops or show off my stomach or my full back or wear a bathing suit top (although we saw all of these by tourists). Does this help at all? —Judy",2025-04-22T14:33:11Z,2025-04-22T14:33:11Z,0,True,,2026-05-15T02:01:54.437279
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg.AH6JcS9XcqKAHDUnluogM_,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Angela, There are no required vaccinations that the Moroccan government checks to see if you have had. However, with the monkeys in the Sahara, it wouldn't be the worst thing to have a rabies vaccination (we do not have that vaccination). We made sure that we had Hepatitis A, B, tetanus, MMR (measles, mumps, and rubella), typhoid, and cholera before we traveled to Egypt. If you have any specific concerns, it's not a bad idea to check with a travel doctor who can give you recommendations. But specific to Morocco? Nothing is required for entry. —Judy
🎥 Why we got vaccinated in Rome before heading to Egypt: https://youtu.be/ZJG4MI76u58
🎥 Morocco Travel Series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNT98lWfwdF0_pL4S2LnqlBz2KBX9XMCc",2025-04-22T13:00:05Z,2025-04-22T13:00:05Z,0,True,,2026-05-15T02:01:54.507160
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg.AH6JcS9XcqKAHDXfrhFZHe,UgyjBXrRN4434_OtEkp4AaABAg,@Roathcourt,@ thank you so much Angela,2025-04-22T13:25:13Z,2025-04-22T13:25:13Z,0,True,,2026-05-15T02:01:54.507171
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugzgj9tbOmptG1mUAcV4AaABAg.AGx6eqm664_AGx71udc2kW,Ugzgj9tbOmptG1mUAcV4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"We loved our time in Morocco! We especially enjoyed Fes, but we spent a month between Marrakech, the Sahara Desert, and Fes. We would definitely like to spend time exploring more of the country. —Judy",2025-04-15T19:05:21Z,2025-04-15T19:05:21Z,0,True,,2026-05-15T02:01:54.562137
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugz1GttXKozX0cZhDqx4AaABAg.AGsAZLPMU1UAGsBwyFqJ6j,Ugz1GttXKozX0cZhDqx4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Syed, You will always be at the mercy of the border agent who you talk to. Offhand, I don't recall that they asked us anything. We may have had to show proof of onward travel afterwards and possibly the address of our riad where we were staying, but nothing else. These are common questions we get asked occasionally, but I think every agent does their own thing. It can also be dependent on your passport, and we are Americans. That's not to say in these unusual times that border agents will continue to be as kind to us. —Judy",2025-04-13T21:12:01Z,2025-04-13T21:12:01Z,0,True,,2026-05-15T02:01:54.615958
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg.AGXs4tM4mb3AGYDb2MBC3R,UgzVBKkk_fCKCGEPjxl4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Thelminetta, Neither of us recalls that we had to do that. Of course, you're always at the mercy of the specific passport security personnel you end up getting and possibly also your passport. You might enjoy our other episodes from our 40+ days in Morocco. —Judy
