Tourism,wFZyNQAIcdE,UgxVm-oUFL2KZwbT3YV4AaABAg,,@richarnold5323,"Hollywood walk of shame has NEVER been shown as ""glamourous"".  It was a marketing money-scheme since Day One.  Who travels 1000 miles without reading reviews about the destination?  It was a dump when I went there in the 80s - people know that, but many want to interact with the local hucksters ... it's part of the lure, just as going to a flea market to haggle is part of it's appeal.  The area is full of theaters, you can tour the Kodak Theater, and there's a Madame Tussad's museum, Ripley's Believe It Or Not musuem, and more.  Lots of sights in the area if you walk around.",2026-05-04T23:43:11Z,2026-05-04T23:45:52Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-15T02:02:20.241125
Tourism,wFZyNQAIcdE,UgxI_LIpUlr_yv_qaZl4AaABAg,,@kimmccarthy7747,"I remember visiting the historic section of Galveston with my mom on a bus tour of Texas.  We were let out at the visitor's center and informed that they were filming a movie in the historic area.  We could go in anyway, if we stayed out of the cameras' way.  Mom and I said, let's go.  We found them filming exterior shots along one street, and located a hamburger stand behind the camera set up.  We had lunch watching them film antique cars and a tram over and over,  talked to a few extras in costume, and took pictures of the cameras and a wagon full of palm trees.  It was great.  When we got back to the visitor's center, we discovered no one else had left the building, scared off by the idea of the camera crew.  A vacation is what you make of it.",2026-05-04T21:16:03Z,2026-05-04T21:16:03Z,3,False,1.0,2026-05-15T02:02:20.241129
