Tourism,tcGjKt8XRTI,UgyBiD8zwEIG-ARK-K54AaABAg,,@michaeldunson2531,When I used to travel with my wife we travel on the off seasons! When I was station in Europe we never vacation during their vacation breaks! There were still people but not like there are doing vacation breaks! When we travel in America we never travel during holidays or when kids was out of school are when colleges was out during spring break! A lot of people like the crowds and people but we traveled to see the sites not the people!,2026-05-13T19:24:03Z,2026-05-13T19:24:03Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-15T02:02:24.567610
Tourism,tcGjKt8XRTI,UgxZMqZmn_0DUjMT06l4AaABAg,,@ninjabookitty,"This is exactly why I travel in the off season. I like the cold and I like blending in so that t isn't readily apparent that I am an American, and by the time they know, I've already been so kind and respectful that it doesn't matter. It's not hard to be welcomed as a visitor. You just have to get over yourself first. Jan/Feb is my sweet spot. No one is traveling because they're broke from the holidays. Lots of great deals to be had.",2026-05-13T17:31:52Z,2026-05-13T17:38:27Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-15T02:02:24.567617
