Tourism,tcGjKt8XRTI,Ugz-7Tpm9ALcIlxnTzV4AaABAg,,@pbjsilverstudio4882,"As the world population continues to grow, this problem will not get better. I have a problem with social media influencers and YouTubers who promote the beautiful and amazing places around the world without also qualifying their information with the realities of what this places are really facing. I moved to another country and we chose a place that was peaceful and beautiful. But it is also a place that is sometimes promoted by YouTubers and our cities is now under so much construction it’s scary. Why? Because it is in a desert and water is a precious commodity. WE are hyper aware of that fact and take GREAT CARE with our water usage. But most foreigners who now live here full or part time don’t even think about it. There are large fountains in some of their homes and lots of swimming pools even though we are surround by or protected water ways and ocean.   Now we see condos going up all over the city and that scares me. I swear it would be better if rich people bough those plots of land and built big fancy homes because it would be just one household using the water, not multiple households who use the water without a thought.",2026-05-06T15:19:26Z,2026-05-06T15:19:26Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-15T02:02:24.568076
Tourism,tcGjKt8XRTI,UgxrYLBgOHFgBMLywG54AaABAg,,@WrldExplorer,"We already did our 10 day trip to Spain last week. We will be back to Europe for three weeks come October, and hopefully for the 
holidays for the Christmas markets. I retired four years ago, and the great thing is I don’t have to go when my job says I can go. So now I travel during shoulder seasons. Some locations will still be crowded regardless, but it won’t be summer crowds with added heat and humidity.",2026-05-06T14:09:50Z,2026-05-06T14:09:50Z,12,False,2.0,2026-05-15T02:02:24.568081
