Tanger,HQnJ1mOgw9E,UgyLKXFzB3hsxvciKv14AaABAg,,@Tangermusic,"LYRICS:

My god you look so beautiful
But you’ve got something on your mind
So just tonight, is it alright
If I can help you to forget?
All of your burden, all your sorrow
Turn it off until tomorrow, but today
We’re gonna be okay

All the mean things your head tells you, forget it
The pressure people give you, forget it
The love, the hate, the pleasure, pain
They matter not right now so
Close your eyes and feel the rhythm, surrender
And let your body start to take over
Our hearts in sync, don't care what people think
The floor is ours to take 

One step forward one step back
Don't be shy and don't hold back
One step forward one step back

You've got me so damn desperate
You're all I want, no counterfeit
So just tonight, is it alright
If you could see just past the light?
Peculiarly drawn to you, this feeling somehow isn't new
I really don't know what to do

Tell me, tell me pretty stranger
Why do you look so familiar?
Dry your tears and smile my dear
Let's dance the night away

Pull me pull me, pull me closer
Kiss me like I won't remember 
Darling let's have no regrets
And dance before we’re strangers once again

What's going on inside your head?
You look at me like I’ve been dead
Why do you call me by a name that doesn’t ring a bell?
Maybe you’ve had too much to drink 
Can’t help but notice that the rings we wear, they're similar
My head, it hurts, it hurts, it hurts!

Now that I see your eyes, they remind me of someone
Now that I recognize the smell of your cologne
Memories of a life that aren't of my own
Echo through my soul

Tell me, tell me pretty stranger
Am I really your familiar?
Dry your tears and smile my dear,
I’m sorry for the pain

Pull me pull me, pull me closer
Kiss me, though I won't remember 
Darling let's have no regrets
And dance before we’re strangers once again

One step forward, one step back
Please don't cry now, don't be sad
One step forward, one step back

One step forward one step back
Don’t you worry I’ll be back
And I’ll love you once again 

Though I cannot remember the somebody
That you have been trying to find in me 
Know I never did forget the love I have for you
So please try not to forget me",2024-08-29T20:04:51Z,2024-08-29T20:04:51Z,492,False,13.0,2026-05-15T02:03:07.040721
